76561197995321987,Recommended,277910,9381730,"Posted: 7 March, 2014",all,KO,"Wanted to say that I like this game very much. I really like the interactive aspect, the sense of accomplishment I get when I discover how to accomplish something. I also like the sense of realism that is evident in the game. I really hope that you somehow create much more content and missions for the game. I think I read some where that a version 2 is in the works, hopefully it will add more content and missions. Very pleased. Keep up the good work.Wanted to say something to individuals who maybe having problems getting the game to run. When you first start the game, if the screen goes black and there is no response via keyboard, it may not be the game. I have been noticing lately that a lot of my games that start automatically in full screen mode do this. So I did a little investigating. It turns out that it is the firewall and virus programs. So if you are using one, you might want to first set you firewall and virus in what is called Game mode. Then once the game starts in full screen you can do one of two things: Leave the firewall and virus in game mode during the duration of play. Or change the game to windowed mode and restart it after setting your firewall and virus back into normal mode. This is not the only game were this has happened so check your firewall and virus settings before writing the game off as broken or buggy. It worked for me. Oh and by the way my hours spent playing the game is incorrect, so don't go by that I always play in steam offline mode if the game lets me, so my play time does not get counted. I have put in a good three days of play."
