76561198115579981,Recommended,277910,9638365,"Posted: 26 March, 2014",all,polaarbunnygirl,"This is a unique simulator. It's a cross between Moonbase Alpha for NASA that is also on Steam, with a bit of Space Engineers thrown in for good measure.  This is about power management and repairing systems, or in this case finish building the systems with no reserve systems to start with.  Almost like your in total survival mode from a bad crash landing, when you find the start of a base to take over.  The part I still don't get is where all the extra habitat modules come from, who installs them if not yourself.In Phase 1 you have to watch everything you do.  Start by opening both hatches to the habitat.  There's no air in there anyways.  Take nearly everything inside, be quick, but rest between trips.  Then carry in the last cases, food and then medical. Shut the outter hatch, then the inner hatch.  Now start by getting the pumps installed, then fallow the items down that same wall.  Lastly get the oxygen scrubber going.  Be sure to eat, drink and relieve yourself in the emergency shelter at the end of the medical bay.Once you do that, head outside and get the generator out back going.  Use the buggy in the shelter for this, but also take the radio and battery cases with you.  As soon as that is working, go to the hydrogen pump station next to the buggy shelter and get those 3 lines attached, now quickly drive to the northwest to the radio tower, careful not to take too steep of a slope, the buggy will get damaged.  Fallow the red marker beacons around the west side of the hill, up to the top.Once you got that going, drive back to the shelter. Once there grab a tool case and repair the buggy, your going to need it in shape later.  Now go inside.  Because your done for the most part.  Now just wait for the air scrubber to get to 10 psi, then shut it off. Now go make sure the pumps and everything else down that wall are working.  As soon as the last machine has 10 in the Meta container, your done.Now I realize that almost sounded like a walk through.  But it helps to understand what it is your doing and why. Phase 1 is the hardest one I have run into yet.  I'v managed to complete it totally in 59 minutes.  There are video's on youtube about this simulator. Watch them.  This is NOT ARMA-2, or WoW.  This is a slow and steady simulator, watch your power management systems and take care of your sim.  Death is so unbecoming.  Never plan for the long haul, worry only about the phase your in.  But try to make sure everything is working and charged before you finish a phase, you take damage and power settings to the next phase.  So far each phase gives more food, so really all you have too do is watch your work order to the letter, manage your power systems, learn to turn some stuff off while something more important is running.This is a lot like a chess match. Only against yourself.  I make my own worst enemy.  LOL  I haven't tried mulitiplayer.  But I'm sure for some, it would be much faster with teammates and each doing one job. It's slow, complicated but entertaining at the same time.  Best played with your own music playing, this is a quiet simulator.If your looking for a nice quiet game to putt-putt around in to waste a few hours, without worring about getting in a multiplayer verse, this is it.  Just remember, ""O"" and F1 are your best friends, use them a lot and often.  They'll help you save your sim's life."
